<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7721> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7721" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis, probably IIIIvir. See MRR 2.198, 446. Dated to 44 also by Crawford (RRC 1.487-495, no. 480). Perhaps the M. Metius (Maecius?) sent by Caesar to parley with Ariovistus (BG 1.47 and 53).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5062> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5062" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Caesar sent them to Ariovistus who made them prisoners. They were freed by Caesar’s victory (Caes. BG 1.47.4-6, and 53.5-8)." .
